articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mahmoud Issa, Dawoud Abu Alkas
articles.description: Many of the hundreds of thousands of Palestinians expected to head back to the northern Gaza Strip will return to homes in ruins.
articles.title: Gazans ready tent camps for families returning to north after ceasefire

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Thursday he wanted to meet Russian President Vladimir Putin as soon as possible to secure an end to the war with Ukraine and expressed a desire to work towards cutting nuclear arms.
articles.title: Trump says he's ready to meet Putin 'immediately' to secure end of Ukraine war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A rapidly growing wildfire broke out some 50 miles (80 km) north of Los Angeles on Wednesday, burning 3,407 acres (5.3 square km) while two major fires burning in the metropolitan area for more than two weeks were getting under control, fire officials said.
articles.title: New wildfire breaks out north of Los Angeles, forces evacuations

articles.author: Daniel Catchpole, Nate Raymond
articles.description: A federal judge blocked Donald Trump's administration on Thursday from implementing the Republican president's executive order curtailing the right to automatic birthright citizenship in the United States, calling it "blatantly unconstitutional."
articles.title: US judge temporarily blocks Trump's order restricting birthright citizenship

articles.author: Sam Tobin, Michael Holden
articles.description: A British teenager who killed three young girls at a Taylor Swift-themed dance event was jailed for at least 52 years on Thursday, for an attack Prime Minister Keir Starmer called one of the most harrowing moments in Britain's history.
articles.title: UK teenager jailed for minimum of 52 years for 'harrowing' Southport girls' murders

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: Russia on Thursday reprimanded the head of the U.N. children's agency UNICEF for not providing a "weighty argument for her refusal" to brief the Security Council on children in Gaza - a meeting requested by Russia.
articles.title: Russia accuses UNICEF head of caring more about kids in Ukraine than Gaza

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: North Korea's Supreme People's Assembly (SPA) met over two days this week and reported on its achievements during 2024 but state media made no mention of anticipated changes to the constitution that would further cement its hostile policy towards South Korea.
articles.title: North Korea's assembly meets but no mention of unification, foreign policy changes

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Moscow Mayor Sergei Sobyanin said early on Friday that air defence units had intercepted attacks by Ukrainian drones at four locations around the Russian capital.
articles.title: Moscow mayor says air defences repel Ukrainian drone attacks aimed at capital

articles.author: Una Galani, Peter Thal Larsen
articles.description: The head of Bangladesh's interim government, Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus, said on Thursday that his country's high growth under ousted Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina was "fake" and faulted the world for not questioning what he said was her corruption.
articles.title: Exclusive: Bangladesh's high growth under ousted PM Hasina was 'fake', interim head Yunus says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 20 fishermen have been killed in Nigeria's northeastern state of Borno after Boko Haram insurgents attacked their village, fishermen and local security officers said on Thursday.
articles.title: Boko Haram militants kill at least 20 in Nigeria's Borno state
